<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 18 at 1:52AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Patchy dense fog expected though mid- morning...
Patchy dense fog has developed in the Helena valley and Northern
Jefferson County this morning. Visibility may fall to a half mile
or less at times.
Anyone traveling should plan on variable visibility down to a
half mile or less at times. Also, frost may develop on roadway
surfaces, causing slippery spots to develop.</description>
